schedule -- composable time-based schedule rules for Go

OVERVIEW

  Package schedule lets you define when a program should be active
  using composable rules: day-of-week, time-of-day, date inclusion/
  exclusion, and date ranges. All rules must match for a time to
  be considered active. Overnight time ranges (e.g. 22:00-02:00)
  are handled correctly across midnight boundaries.

USAGE (CODE)

  s := schedule.New(
      schedule.Weekdays(),
      schedule.ExceptDates("2026-01-01", "2026-12-25"),
      schedule.TimeRange("07:00", "19:00"),
  )

  s.Match(time.Now())       // true if now is in schedule
  s.Watch()                 // SIGTERM self when schedule ends
  s.Wait()                  // block until schedule is active

USAGE (JSON)

  s, err := schedule.Parse(jsonBytes)

  {
    "days": "weekdays",
    "time_range": ["07:00", "19:00"],
    "except_dates": ["2026-01-01", "2026-12-25"]
  }

  "days" accepts "weekdays", "weekends", or an array:
  ["monday", "wednesday", "friday"]

RULES

  Weekdays()              Mon-Fri
  Weekends()              Sat-Sun
  Days(time.Weekday...)   specific weekdays
  TimeRange(from, to)     clock window, "HH:MM" format
                          supports overnight (e.g. "22:00", "02:00")
  ExceptDates(dates...)   exclude "YYYY-MM-DD" dates
  OnlyDates(dates...)     match only specific dates
  DateRange(start, end)   match date range inclusive
  Not(rule)               invert any rule
  RuleFunc(fn)            custom rule from func(time.Time) bool

METHODS

  Match(t time.Time) bool
      Returns true if t satisfies all rules.

  Window(t time.Time) (start, end time.Time, ok bool)
      Returns the start and end of the active window containing t.

  Next(t time.Time) (time.Time, bool)
      Returns the next minute at or after t where the schedule
      becomes active. Scans up to 400 days.

  ActiveUntil(t time.Time) (time.Time, bool)
      Returns the last contiguous active minute from t.

  Watch()
      Background goroutine. Sends SIGTERM when schedule ends.
      Panics after 30s if process does not exit.

  Wait()
      Blocks until the schedule becomes active.

OVERNIGHT SCHEDULES

  TimeRange("22:00", "02:00") with Weekdays() means:

    Fri 22:00 - Sat 02:00    active (started on Friday)
    Sat 22:00 - Sun 02:00    inactive (Saturday is not a weekday)
    Sun 22:00 - Mon 02:00    inactive (Sunday is not a weekday)
    Mon 22:00 - Tue 02:00    active (started on Monday)

  Day/date rules are evaluated against the day the window started,
  not the current calendar day.

JSON CONFIG FIELDS

  days          string or []string    day-of-week filter
  time_range    [string, string]      clock window "HH:MM"
  except_dates  []string              excluded dates "YYYY-MM-DD"
  only_dates    []string              included dates only
  date_range    [string, string]      date range inclusive
  not           bool                  invert entire schedule
